laboratory_examinations.findings: Very few mononuclear cells, no white or red cells. Levels of glucose, total protein, and angiotensin-converting enzyme were normal. No organisms on Gram staining. No oligoclonal bands or malignant cells.
Hematocrit, hemoglobin level, white-cell count, differential count, and platelet count were normal.
Blood levels of electrolytes, calcium, phosphorus, magnesium, glucose, C-reactive protein, angiotensin-converting enzyme, and immunoglobulins (IgG, IgA, and IgM) were normal.
1+ ketones, trace occult blood, and protein by dipstick, with 0 to 2 red cells, very few renal tubular cells, few squamous cells, and mucin per low-power field.

Positive for anti-Ro antibodies (63.37; reference range, 0 to 19.99) and antinuclear antibodies (at 1:40 and 1:160 dilutions, in a homogeneous pattern); negative for antineutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies (anti-PR3 and anti-MPO), anti-La antibodies, and anti-double-stranded DNA antibodies.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Biopsy of left posterior ethmoid and sphenoid sinuses
laboratory_examinations.findings: Sinonasal mucosa with underlying dense lymphoid infiltrate in a background of fibrosis. Large lymphoid cells positive for CD20, confirming diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.
